<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SBAC Wins Sector Challenge Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Society of British Aerospace
Companies (SBAC) has been awarded a 1.5 million pounds (2.4
million US dollars) grant by the Government to further improve the
competitiveness in the UK aerospace industry.
</P>
<P>
The grant is the largest of thirty winning projects in the
Government's Sector Challenge which is an inter-departmental
initiative led by the Department of Trade &AMP; Industry to enhance
the competitiveness of the British engineering industry.
</P>
<P>
Under the Competitiveness Challenge program, some 500 aerospace
organizations, mainly small and medium enterprises, have
participated and 200 of them have become full members of the
program and regularly contribute to its activities.
</P>
<P>
The grant is a praise of SBAC's success in the areas of supply
chain development, people management, business winning,
engineering and manufacturing innovation and knowledge management.
</P>
<P>
The Challenge has been highly successful in instigating
industry led projects worth over 2 million pounds (3.2 million US
dollars), generating over 10,000 man days of effort and
stimulating 12 major team-based activities, SBAC said in a
statement released today.
</P>
<P>
Through its activities and commitment from industry, the
Challenge is establishing itself as the aerospace industry focus
for tackling competitiveness issues, it added.
</P>
<P>
The SBAC is the trade association for the UK aerospace
industry. It represents 2.5 percent of the nation's manufacturing
capability and employs 110,000 highly-skilled personnel.
</P>
<P>
Seventy percent of SBAC's annual turnover of 11 billion pounds
(1.76 billion US dollars) is exported, and it has contributed an
average 2 billion pounds (3.2 billion US dollars) to the UK
balance of payments every year in the past decade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
