<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA -- Congo's capital of Brazzaville was in its third day
of clashes between supporters of ex-president Denis Sassou Nguesso
and troops loyal to President Pascal Lissouba, sources said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Damascus Declaration signatory states' foreign
ministers will meet in the Syrian capital late this month to
discuss the Mideast peace process, the Egyptian MENA news agency
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The Afghan Islamic Taliban militia Saturday
recaptured a strategic town north of Kabul from the opposing
factions after four hours of heavy fighting, sources said.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A Palestinian-Israeli expert meeting will be held here
Sunday to tackle the Jewish settlements and other important issues
on the Mideast peace process, Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- The coupists that toppled Sierra Leone's legitimate
government led by President Tejan Kabbah called on Friday for
dialogue to end the crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwait's leading newspapers Saturday all
condemned the assassination attempt on parliamentary member
Abuddullah Al-Neibari's life Friday in their front pages and
described the crime as an ugly act against the nation. 
</P>
