<HEADLINE> Somali Factions Opposing Aidid Warn Against Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 7 (Xinhua)- Three factions opposing Somali
faction leader Hussein Mohamed Aidid last night issued a decree
Warning against use of the recently arrived consignment of Somali
Shilings for the government of Hussein Aidid in South Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
In the decree, the factions led by Ali Mahdi Mohamed, Osman
Hassan Ali Atto and Abdullahi Ossoble allied with Ali Mahdi
warned the Somali business connunities to refrain from the use of
the money which they characterized as " fake". It also warned the
Somalis that this money will lead them to a full bankruptcy and
that those found possessing and using the money will be taken to
the courts.
</P>
<P>
It said this money will four fold the current inflation of the
Somali Shilling.
</P>
<P>
The three factions have prohibited the circulation of this
money in the areas under their control.
</P>
<P>
The decree alerted the Islamic courts militiamen and the
security personnel to take the necessary measures in stopping the
propagation of this money.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the decree, the Islamic courts of North
Mogadishu controlled by Ali Mahdi Mohamed today caught three
people possessing the newly printed money in Karan Market.
</P>
<P>
The supreme court has sentenced the three men each five years
imprisonment and confiscated the money which valued three
thousand Somali shillings.
</P>
<P>
Store owners in Bakara market today stopped selling their
goods in Somali Shillings as come of the newly printed money has
reached the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
