<HEADLINE> France Supports Gabon in Mediating Clash in Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- France today express support to the
mediation offered by President Omar Bongo of Gabon to end the
on-going clash in Congo between President Pacal Lissouba and
former President Denis Sassou Nguesso in Brazzaville.
</P>
<P>
"France supports the mediation by President Congo which should
allow the democratic process (of Congo) to continue," said French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
President Bongo Friday launched an appeal to the Congolese to
"mute the sound of gun shots"and seek a solution to the conflict
"through dialogue."
</P>
<P>
The French ambassador in Brazzaville is keeping contact with
the Congolese authorities and the 4,000-strong French community
living in Congo, an important oil exporter to France.
</P>
<P>
Fighting went on for a third consecutive day today between the
government forces and the militias supporting Nguesso in the
capital.
</P>
<P>
Congo is scheduled to hold its presidential election on July 27
in which both Lissouba and Nguesso are supposed to run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
