<HEADLINE> Beijing Show For Hong's Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A long tone poem that combines song
and dance to celebrate Hong Kong's return to the motherland was
performed this evening at Beijing's International Theater in the
Poly Plaza.
</P>
<P>
This was the first performance of the work, which is called
"Beijing Wishes You Well, Hong Kong". It will be performed again
in Tian'anmen Square on June 30, on the eve of Hong Kong's
return. It consists of four movements: Missing, Yearning,
Celebration and Splendor, and includes 16 songs.
</P>
<P>
The work depicts the century of longing of the Chinese people
for Hong Kong, their enthusiasm about Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, and good wishes of the people of Beijing for Hong
Kong's return. It involves more than 500 artists.
</P>
<P>
The work was composed with the help of the publicity department
of the municipal Party committee, the general office of the
municipal government, and Beijing TV. 
</P>
</TEXT>
