<HEADLINE> Train Collision Kills One in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and two
others injured when a freight train rear-ended a coal train in
West Virginia Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred 10 miles to Charleston, West Virginia.
</P>
<P>
Several cars on the freight train carried automobile parts that
burned brightly hours after the crash. Authorities feared the
flames would spread to other cars carrying bleach, sulfuric acid
and other chemicals.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people were in a hollow where the only road out was
blocked by flaming wreckage. The residents were told to stay
inside their homes with their windows closed.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of other residents within two miles of the crash site
fled their homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
