<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Beat Japan 3-0 in World League Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria smashed Japan's hopes
of winning a place in the final stage of the world league men's
volleyball tournament, scoring a three-set win in a preliminary
Group A match in Hiroshima, Japan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria overpowered Japan with a 15-8, 16-14, 15-3 victory for
its sixth win against two defeats in the four-team preliminary
contest.
</P>
<P>
In four consecutive wins over Japan, Bulgaria has dropped only
one set and that was the first set in a match Saturday when they
were suffering the effects of jetlag.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria also have two wins over Argentina while losing twice
to Barcelona Olympic champions Brazil.
</P>
<P>
It was a humiliating eighth straight defeat for the Japanese
and even if they could beat Brazil and Argentina twice each in
their remaining matches, a finals berth is now out of reach.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria will take on Brazil in away games next weekend, while
Japan will play Argentina in Osaka. 
</P>
