<HEADLINE> Sufficient Funds In Shanghai's Money Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Turnover in China's inter-bank
business hit 74.9 billion yuan during the first five months of
this year, up 19 percent from the same period last year, according
to the Shanghai fund center.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the increase to sufficient funds coming from
the issuing of treasury bonds, recalling discount loans to
commercial banks by the central bank, and the steady increase in
savings deposits.
</P>
<P>
This is tied to the continuous drop in interest rates this
year, which averaged 0.43 percentage points in the past five
months, while financial institutions have turned to short-term
loans at a reduced rate.
 
</P>
