<HEADLINE> World's Top Fiberglass Maker Now In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The US's Owens-Corning Company,
the largest fiberglass manufacturer in the world, set up a joint
venture with the Shanghai Building Materials (Group) Corporation
on Friday, in China's largest business center.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 30 million US dollars was put into the joint venture,
which is designed to produce heat- and noise-proof products for
housing and industrial buildings.
</P>
<P>
The new firm has a yearly capacity of 12,000 tons of insulation
material. Its raw materials will mainly come from waste glass
collected locally.
</P>
<P>
The American company already has joint ventures in the cities
of Changchun, Guangzhou, Anshan and Nanjing, with a total
investment of nearly 100 million US dollars in them. 
