<HEADLINE> S. Africa Expects More Blacks Driving Train </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- More black people will be
seen operating passenger trains in South Africa, local daily City
Press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen black drivers successfully completed their nine-month
training in Feburary this year and will receive driving
certificates in the next two weeks, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The new staff will bring the number of black train drivers
qualified to drive passenger trains to 18 -- two other black
drivers are already on the job.
</P>
<P>
According to communication department officials, some 180
black train drivers will be eventually trained throughout South
Africa in coming years. 
</P>
