<HEADLINE> Morocco Reaches World Cup Football Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Morocco became the first
African nation to enter the World Cup football finals four times
after beating Ghana 1-0 in a qualifier game in Casablanca this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Lions of the Atlas qualified for the 1970, 1986 and 1994
finals and French coach Henri Michel will take them to his country
next June for the first 32-nation tournament.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Saturday, Nigeria had become the first qualifiers
for the World Cup finals by outclassing South Kenya 3-0 in Lagos.
</P>
<P>
Africa will have five finalists for the first time and two more
places could be filled on Sunday if Tunisia avoid defeat in Egypt
and Cameroon win in Angola. 
</P>
