<HEADLINE> CIS Parliaments Appeal for Unity and Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Top lawmakers from nine former
Soviet republics called today for greater unity and cooperation
within the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), ITAR-TASS
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Nine of CIS's 12 members took part in the interparliamentary
assembly held in St. Petersburg, Russia, an annual meeting to
coordinate the work of their parliaments.
</P>
<P>
"We have given up attempts to find happiness abroad and are
looking more closely at each other," Russian upper house speaker
Yegor Stroyev told the assembly.
</P>
<P>
Delegations from Azerbaijan, Armenia, Belarus, Georgia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Moldova, Russia and Tajikistan attended
the assembly. Ukraine's legislators took part in as observers.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan is the only CIS member state that has chosen to be
out of the parliamentary assembly, while Uzbekistan, although a
member of assembly, was absent this time. 
</P>
