<HEADLINE> Ramos Wants Philippines to Be Fully Industrialized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
said today that the country should not be content with being
merely industrializing, but must become fully industrialized.
</P>
<P>
President Ramos raised this goal when delivering a keynote
speech at a national development conference aimed at working out a
strategy that can help the country pole-vault into the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
"We must not just alleviate poverty, we must eradicate it. We
must not be content with being merely industrializing, we must
become fully industrialized," he said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this goal, the country should work out a
pole-vaulting program that identifies the economic and political
reform still undone in the country and some programs that must be
accomplished over a specific period, Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of various sectors of the country should also sustain
the forward drive of all reforms to successfully overcome the
poverty of Filipino families and expand the circle of economic
progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the country should work hard to catch up its
East Asian neighbors and ensure the economy's competitiveness in
the global market by making it an efficient creator of wealth, he
said.  
</P>
