<HEADLINE> Macedonian President Leaves for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov
today left Skoplje, capital of Macedonian Republic, for China for
a five-day state visit at the invitation of Chinese President
Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Before departure, Gligorov, at the Skoplje airport, said that
his Chinese tour is a great event in the relations between
Macedonia and China and Macedonia attaches great importance to it.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy to have a chance to meet and talk with Chinese
leaders," he said. "I believe my visit will be successful and help
further develop the bilateral relations between the two
countries."
</P>
<P>
Gligorov's visit to China is the first one by a Macedonian
president. China and Macedonia, though geographically wide apart,
enjoys a long tradition of friendship. Bilateral cooperation in
politics, the economy, culture, science and technology has
proceeded smoothly since diplomatic relations were established in
October 1993.
</P>
<P>
During Gligorov's visit, the two nations will sign agreements
on investment protection and avoiding double taxation. 
