<HEADLINE> South China Win Hong Kong's Soccer League Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- South China won over defending
champions Instant-Dict 3-2 in the extra-time of the Hong Kong
soccer First Division League Grand Final here Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It is the first League title for South China in five seasons.
</P>
<P>
Instant-Dict won this year's Hong Kong FA Cup just a week ago.
</P>
<P>
South China had an edge over Instant-Dict, with four wins, two
draws and one loss, in the seven previous meetings this season
between the two sides. But only once in the five decisive matches
between the two this season had more than one goal to separate the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
"We've played each other so often that each team knows the
other's style of play inside out," South China striker Dale
Tempest told a local newspaper. "So I don't think you're are going
 to see a high-score game come on Sunday," he predicted.
</P>
<P>
With skipper and veteran defender Ku Kam-fai out of the match
because of a thigh injury suffered last month, South China's
defense had suffered a lot, which was clearly shown in today's
match, especially in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Ross Greer of Instant-Dict opened the score at the 11th minute
when his sharply-angled slide shot beat South China's goalkeeper
Kooistra Werner out of balance.
</P>
<P>
South China leveled the score 13 minutes later when Tempest's
shot from inside the goal area found the net.
</P>
<P>
Instant-Dict made it 2-1 in the 42nd minute when a shot by Paul
Foster deflected on a defender's foot and flew into the goal.
</P>
<P>
And in the dying minute of the match, South China tied it
again, with a close-range header by forward Cheng Siu-chung.
</P>
<P>
It was Cheng again when he converted a corner-kick by his
teammate with another close-range header, at the 17th minute of
the extra time. It sealed up South China's victory as the match
was played on the "Golden Goal" concept, which means that any team
which scores the fist goal in the extra time, win the match.
</P>
<P>
Scorers:
</P>
<P>
Instant-Dict: Ross Greer (11th minute); Paul Foster (42nd);
</P>
<P>
South China: Dale Tempest (24th), Ricky Cheng Siu-chung (46th,
17th of extra time).  
</P>
</TEXT>
