<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- France will send 500 more soldiers to
the Congo Republic from Monday, the Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The two companies of troops would be sent from French military
bases in the region, Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux
said, apparently referring to French garrisons in Gabon and the
Central African Republic.
</P>
<P>
A cellular team on the Congo crisis met today to discuss
reaction to the escalating violence in Brazzaville after one
French soldier was killed and five others wounded in a clash with
"uncontrollable armed elements" in Congo Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
The 450 French soldiers previously stationed in Brazzaville
have been escorting some 4,000 French expatriates in Congo to the
French Embassy and other French missions, but no immediate plan of
evacuation is worked out.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry announced earlier today that it is sending
armored vehicles to Congo Republic.
</P>
<P>
Fighting broke out Thursday morning between government troops
and private militiamen supporting former President Denis
Sassou-Nguesso, after his residence was reportedly attacked by the
army. 
</P>
