<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 10 Injured in Traffic Accident in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Eight passengers, two of them
children, were killed and 10 others injured in a collision
involving a stage bus and a mini bus near Sandakan, Sabah, East
Malaysia, Saturday, according to a local report today.
</P>
<P>
The dead are all Indonesians, the Malaysian national news
agency Bernama reported quoting police officer Brahim Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The stage bus with 30 passengers was on its way from Kota
Kinabalu, Sabah's capital, when it collided with a mini bus with
15 people onboard while trying to avoid a pot hole, the police
officer said.
</P>
<P>
The mini bus was badly smashed in the collision and the mini
bus driver and seven passengers died.
</P>
<P>
The survivors, who are rushed to a local hospital for
treatment, were said to be in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Two of the 30 passengers in the stage bus and the driver were
injured and given outpatient treatment. The others escaped unhurt.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
