<HEADLINE> 17-year-old Ma Beats Two-time World Cup Winner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Teenager Ma Lin upset two-time
World Cup winner Ma Wenge in the final of the China All-star Table
Tennis Tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Ma, who plays in penhold style and an
aggressive top-spin game, nipped his 29-year-old namesake 21-18,
21-19, 21-17.
</P>
<P>
Ma Lin began to play table tennis at age 6 and jumped into fame
after winning the Yugoslavia Open last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yong, a sparring partner for Chinese top players and
himself the reigning national singles champion, downed 1995 world
champion and World Cup winner Kong Linghui 21-16, 21-14 in the
best-of-three third-place playoff.
</P>
<P>
World No. 9 Wang Chen overcame Cui Chenmei 21-15, 18-21, 20-22,
21-12, 21-10 to win the women's singles title.
</P>
<P>
Cui, 20, had been virtually unknown before she upset world
runner-up Wang Nan in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Yang Ying, the best women penholder in the world, defeated
Zhang Hui 21-16, 21-15 to take the third place. 
</P>
