<HEADLINE> China Continues to Be Ideal Place for Overseas Investment, Scholar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China is likely to be an ideal
place for overseas investment in the next century, with a prospect
of attracting 30 to 40 billion US dollars of foreign funds
annually, according to a local academician.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zhongli, President of the Shanghai Academy of Social
Sciences, recently said here that China is a big attraction to the
rest of the world, as its economy shows prospects of a high-speed
growth and the country's 1.2 billion-strong population creates a
huge market.
</P>
<P>
In general, foreign investment in China has turned from the
previous labor-intensive industries to technology-intensive
sectors, he said, adding that transnationals and giants have
become the major foreign investors in the country.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that more international firms will move their
regional headquarters to China, and Shanghai is the most ideal
place to locate them.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, now with over 16,000 foreign-funded projects, is the
largest economic center in China. The metropolis has nearly 1,000
research institutes and 900,000 professionals, according to
official figures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
