<HEADLINE> India's Coffee Prices to Be Raised Again Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The prices of coffee at the
retail outlets in India are to be increased by 10 rupees (0.28 US
dollar) per kg from next Monday, making it the fifth rise since
February this year, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Coffee prices were last raised by 10 rupees per kg from 180
rupees (5.14 dollars) per kg on May 26.
</P>
<P>
The prices of the commodity have spurted since February due to
mixed reasons of rise in international prices, low stocks with
traders and a shortfall in domestic consumption.
</P>
<P>
A steep hike in coffee prices was witnessed during last week of
May following the Association of Coffee Producing Countries'
decision to continue their curb on exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
