<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 0830 GMT, June 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Over 60 people were killed and 200 others injured
when a huge fire broke out at the Thanjavur temple in Tamil Nadu
of southern India Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
The fire was caused when some airborne crackers fell into the
temple and ignited the oil vessels and the pandal, which was
already dry due to extreme hot temperature.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashikim Fino on Saturday
asked the Multinational Protection Force (MPF) to extend its
mandate in his country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a cabinet session, Fino asked the Italian-led MPF
to stay three months after its current mandate runs out on June
28, to create a secure environment for the general election to be
held on June 29 and the work of the international observers.
</P>
<P>
SARAJEVO -- Foreign ministers from 16 Central European
countries ended their two-day meeting here on Saturday, pledging
to assist Bosnia's reconstruction efforts.
</P>
