<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Salim to Reform OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Organisation of African
Unity (OAU) Secretary General, Salim Ahmed Salim, on Saturday
said that his immediate task will be to restructure the African
body in line with current responsibilities and challenges.
</P>
<P>
Salim was talking to the press at the International Press
Center in the city, on his way to Ethiopia from the just ended
Harare summit which elected him the OAU Secretary General for the
third time.
</P>
<P>
"We have to look at how best we can have maximum performance
but within our limited resource," he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim said, "We must have the right people at the right place
and choose priorities among prioirities for more effectiveness."
</P>
<P>
He said apart from administrative changes, reforms should also
be made on the continental body's charter for more effective
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief said, his role at his third governance is to
ensure that the OAU constitution is restructured to suit new
challenges and responsibilites in the continent.
</P>
<P>
"Given the budget constraints that the organisation suffers,
it is not easy to change the constitution," he said. However, he
said, "we want the organisation to become dynamic."
</P>
<P>
Salim said his organisation is determined to ensure that
people are involved in the democratisation process in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
The democratisation process in the member countries cannot be
realized unless they involve people in determining what they best
want, he said.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief said it is high time that OAU became modern in
its conduct. "The environment has very much changed in Africa, we
want to ensure democratic societies in the continent," he said.
</P>
<P>
OAU is also determned to consolidate a mutual relationship
with civil societies all over the continent, Salim said.
</P>
<P>
He said Non-Governmental Organisations (NGOs) play a big role
in ensuring that governments are responsible to their citizens,
adding that the aim of the OAU is to work with NGOs in order to
ensure that the African continent is in a safe float.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief further said during the coming four years, the
OAU will be committed at consolidating African unity by ensuring
that proper strategies are designed to prevent conflicts rather
than waiting until they erupt.
</P>
<P>
The organisation will also engage itself in the global
economy, he said, adding that integration is very important if
Africa is to effectively compete in the global economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
