<HEADLINE> Work on Zanzibar Sewers Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Work on the improvement of
the sewerage system at the Zanzibar Central Market, also to cover
the Darajani commercial area, in the town of Zanzibar, has
started, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The project is being financed by a 3.295 million US Dollars
grant by a German Bank - KFW.
</P>
<P>
A sewerage and drainage department official told reporters in
the town on Saturday that the waste water will be spilled a
distance of 372 meters from the shore, a measure taken to avoid
spoiling the environment.
</P>
<P>
The new pipeline will be two meters wide compared to the
present dilapidated one which measures half-a-meter and was
installeld almost half a century back.
</P>
<P>
The project has come following the failure by municipal
authorities to effect waste water treatment as planned due to
non-availability of an oxidation pond attributed to "technical
reaons".
</P>
<P>
Th many years, the area has been one of the dirtiest spots in
Zanzibar town as the sewerage system could not cope with the
increase in population and growth of business.
</P>
<P>
The project is also seen by residents in the town as positive
move towards keeping the environment clean especially during this
period when the Isles have been hit hard by the outbreak of
cholera.
</P>
<P>
The program runs parallet with the rehabilitation of Zanzibar
narrow streets which is now in its final stages for completion
funded by another German company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
