<HEADLINE> Nepal to Promote Cottage Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Nepal will take measures to
promote the exports of cottage and small industry products to
create jobs and alleviate poverty, press reports here said today.
</P>
<P>
To that end, the government will list the development of
cottage and small industries in the forthcoming Ninth Plan,
scheduled to start in July, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The government will also provide raw materials to cottage
industries, help enhance their managerial skills and offer
additional facilities.
</P>
<P>
As the cottage and small industries play an important role in
strengthening the country's economy, the government has decided to
increase investment in this sector, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal Rastra Bank, the country's central bank, has been issuing
soft loans to the cottage and small industries.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment in 1990, the Federation of Nepal
Cottage and Small Industries has provided skill-oriented training
to 1,200 persons in fashion designing, sewing and weaving, radio
and TV repairs.  
</P>
