<HEADLINE> Good Chance for Peace in Afghanistan: Turkmenistan FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Boris Shikhmuradov said here today there was a
good chance for all neighboring countries to evolve a formula for
lasting peace in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen before his departure this morning,
Shikhmuradov said he held useful talks with Pakistani leaders and
expressed optimism about strengthening bilateral relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We have no contradictions with Pakistan over regional and
bilateral issues," he said. "Pakistan is a friendly and brotherly
country."
</P>
<P>
Replying to a question about the possibility of recognizing the
Taliban by Turkmenistan, he said, "We respect the territorial
integrity, independence and stability in Afghanistan, which is
very important for us."
</P>
<P>
"Turkmenistan is a UN member and would strictly follow all UN
rules and regulations," he added.
</P>
<P>
Shikhmuradov said "we fully understand moves initiated by
Pakistan and wish a settlement soon in Afghanistan."
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the need for all Afghan factions and ethnic
groups to come to the negotiation table and said that the Afghan
issue can only be solved through intra-Afghan dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The Turkmenistan foreign minister said that after talks with
Pakistani leaders on this important issue, next time he will visit
Teheran to hold discussions with Iranian authorities.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan would
