<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe
appealed his people to remain united to ensure peace and
development in the country.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when celebrating vice-president Joshua
Nkomo's 80th birthday in Bulawayo, the country's second largest
city, yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe praised Nkomo for the contribution he made towards the
liberation struggle and his role in forging unity between Zanu
(PF) and pr-Zapu in 1987.
</P>
<P>
