that we should remain united as one nation."
</P>
<P>
The president said after all the years of struggling to
liberate the country, Nkomo was still worried that the land
question had not yet been resolved. He promised that his
government would do everything within its power to acquire enough
land to cater for the landless.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to assure you that my government will address
the land question once and for all this year. We have a
committee, being led by Joseph Msika, which is identifying farms
to be acquired to resettle the landless," said Mugabe. 
