<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino Weather Phenomenon Arrives in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The "El Nino" phenomenon has arrived
in the Peruvian coasts, a report from the National Meteorology
and Hydrology Service said today.
</P>
<P>
The temperature of the sea water in some zones is four degrees
centigrade higher than in the surrounding masses of the ocean
waters, while the atmospheric pressures are too high, said Jose
Ames Ruiz, director of the service.
</P>
<P>
Ruiz said that the direction of the winds has reversed and
changed their course toward the continent. The El Nino phenomenon
will bring strong rains to the north and drought in the southern
areas in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said the El Nino in the 1982-1984 caused 600 million U.S.
dollars in losses because of the flood in the north of Peru, and a
lost of some 250 million dollars in southern Peru because of the
drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
