<DOCNO> XIE19970608.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rail Line to HK To Help Boost Shenzhen Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen will be able to co-operate
closely with areas along the Beijing Kowloon Railway line because
the first train from Beijing to Kowloon entered Hong Kong via the
north-south trunk line in mid-May, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Experts from local organizations, including the Shenzhen
Comprehensive Development Institute, believe that more
co-operation is expected in communications and transportation,
business transfer, market and resource development and the use of
overseas funds between Shenzhen and the interior areas.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that Shenzhen, which is near Hong Kong and a
pioneer in China's opening-up drive, will become a successful
service center for overseas businesses investing in interior
areas, especially those along the Beijing Kowloon line.
</P>
<P>
The city, with 12 national exit and entry checkpoints by sea,
land and air, has standard and efficient services in finance,
information, personnel training, transportation and storage.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon line crosses seven provinces and two
municipalities from north to south, affecting 117 million people.
The areas along the line have abundant natural resources and great
potential for economic development.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, as a major stop on the southern end of the
north-south line, had used 11.87 billion US dollars of overseas
funds by the end of 1996, including investment from more than 130
international consortia and transnationals.
</P>
<P>
The city has spent 2.49 billion yuan (300 million US dollars)
on 866 projects along the route. Those areas invested 4.99 billion
yuan (601 million US dollars) in Shenzhen, with Beijing and
Tianjin far ahead in investment scale.
</P>
<P>
Economic and technical co-operation between Shenzhen and
interior areas previously had been confined to trade, commerce and
real estate.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Interior areas supported Shenzhen's economic
expansion by securing funds and providing advanced technology and
skilled labor.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shenzhen made advanced economic and technological
progress in the interior by launching solely funded businesses,
setting up joint ventures and leasing, trading and taking over
property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
