<HEADLINE> CPV's Third Plenum to Be Held Within Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV)
is to discuss ways of building and consolidating the state and
selecting qualified personnel for the period of industrialization
and modernization at the coming third plenum of its Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The CPV Central Committee has for months sent draft documents
to be discussed at the third plenum to experts and leading
officials of economic sectors at the central and local levels for
comments and suggestions, the Vietnam News Agency (VNA) quoted the
Vietnam Courier Weekly as saying.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here said the third plenum will be opened in
a few days.
</P>
<P>
Conferences have been held at the central level and in major
cities throughout the country to collect opinions from the
participants on two main documents for the coming plenum.
</P>
<P>
The first document is "Continuing to Build and Perfect the
State Apparatus of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam of the
People, for the People and by the People" and the second is "the
Personnel Strategy for the Period of Industrialization and
Modernization, and the Task from Now to the 9th Party Congress."
</P>
<P>
The report said high on the agenda of the next plenum is how to
satisfactorily carry out the resolution of the 8th national party
congress on promoting the people's right to the masters of the
country and to build and perfect the state apparatus. 
</P>
