<HEADLINE> Red Wings Takes NHL Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Detroit Red Wings beat
Philadephia 2-1 Saturday to win their first Stanley Cup
championship since 1955 in Detroit, Michigan.
</P>
<P>
Detroit, who swept the National Hockey League finals in four
games, ended the longest title drought in the NHL, 42 years, and
made team coach Scotty Bowman the first man to coach three
different teams to the championship.
</P>
<P>
Detroit goaltender Mike Vernon won the Conn Smythe Trophy as
the Most Valuable Player of the NHL playoffs. He had a 1.70
goals-against average in the post-season and became the 11th
goaltender to win the award.  
