<HEADLINE> Albania Asks Multinational Force to Stay Three More Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashikim
Fino today asked the Multinational Protection Force (MPF) to
extend its mandate in his country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a cabinet session, Fino asked the Italian-led MPF
to stay three months after its current mandate runs out on
June 28 in an effort to create a secure environment for the
general election to be held on June 29 and the work of the
international observers.
</P>
<P>
Fino instructed the Foreign Ministry to negotiate the extension
of the mandate with related international organizations.
</P>
<P>
On March 28, the United Nations Security Council authorized the
MPF a three-month mandate to protect relief operations and help
restore order in Albania, where massive protests prompted by
collapsed savings schemes turned into armed unrest early this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
