<HEADLINE> Brief Latin American Cultural News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are news related
to cultural events that occurred in the last few days:
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The film "Sol de Otono" got three of the most
coveted awards of the Silver Condor 96 prizes: the best film, the
best director (Eduardo Mignogna) and the best actor (Federico
Luppi).
</P>
<P>
The Argentine Association of Cinema Feature Writers held on
June 2 the awarding of the Silver Condor Prizes 96, the most
important reward of Argentine cinema.
</P>
<P>
The same ceremony celebrated the centennial of the Argentine
cinema industry.
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- The 1997 Summer Festival started Friday in
the Simon Bolivar Metropolitan Park of Santafe de Bogota with a
concert offered by Italian singer Laura Pausini.
</P>
<P>
Bogota residents can attend free of charge during the festival
that lasts 10 days sports events and exhibitions, puppet shows,
the Book Festival and the Naturist Gastronomic Festival, among
other cultural activities.
</P>
<P>
The festival was organized by the District Institute for
Entertainment and Sports of Santafe de Bogota.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Outstanding personalities of the Uruguayan
artistic world got together recently in the city of San Jose to
commemorate the 85th anniversary of the Bartolome Maccio Theater.
</P>
<P>
The festivities, which started on May 31 and will end on June 8
-- the day of the anniversary, include music and ballet
spectacles, theater works and paintings exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
The theater, founded in 1912, was declared national historical
monument in 1984.
</P>
</TEXT>
