<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Film Maker to Remain Strong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China's largest film maker, China
Lucky Film Corp., said it is able to remain strong in the domestic
market following the entrace to China of the US-based Kodak and
Japan's Fuji, According to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident of rooting a strong position in the Chinese
market," said Li Yaochang, manager of Lucky's import and export
department.
</P>
<P>
He reminded his employees about the Three Kingdoms era (AD
220-280) when three independent powers ruled China for a half
century.
</P>
<P>
"Lucky's sales of film and photographic paper in the domestic
and international markets keep rising," Li said, noting that his
company occupied 20 percent of the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Company figures show that film sales grew 20 percent and
photographic paper sales rose 70 percent in 1996, with foreign
exchange earnings reaching 9.1 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, film sales soared 52
percent, photographic paper sales climed 7.9 percent and foreign
exchange earnings rose 26 percent, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Lucky aims to make 10 million US dollars in
foreign exchange this year. He also said that Lucky is preparing
to open 1,000 franchise stores in major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
Although many industry insiders say that Lucky does not lag
behind foreign competitors in film quality, it is difficult to
find developers that can process Lucky film. So many Chinese
customers switched to foreign brands because most developing shops
process those brands.
</P>
<P>
Facing the same money constraints as many State enterprises,
Lucky intends to list on the stock market this year. But Li
declined to give details about listing.
</P>
<P>
Li said Lucky would not reject the possibility of setting up
joint ventures or cooperating with foreign partners, but Lucky
must be the controlling shareholder and the technology transferred
to the venture must be top-notch.
</P>
<P>
The most important condition is that the brand must be Lucky,
Li noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
