<DOCNO> XIE19970608.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New County Seat Being Built in Southwestern Jiangxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Xiajiang County, one of the
relatively-poor areas in southwestern Jiangxi Province, has made
progress in building a new county seat believed to be able to help
link itself to other parts of China via Beijing-Kowloon Railway.
</P>
<P>
Xiajiang, which falls under the jurisdiction of Ji'an
Prefecture, has its existing county seat in Baqiu Town,
located on western bank of the Ganjiang River.
</P>
<P>
The new county seat is being built in Shuibian Town on the
eastern bank of the river, where the north-south trunk rail route
passes and a train stop has been established.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, some 200 million yuan (24 million
US dollars) have so far been spent on the construction, with the
completion of a number of major infrastructure projects, including
an office mansion for Xiajiang County Party Committee and the
county government, and a highly-elevated flyover crossing the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway Line.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the construction pledged that they
would redouble their efforts and step up construction so that the
local county authorities are expected to move into new offices
built in the new county seat by July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
