<HEADLINE> Sino-Macedonian Relations Develop Healthily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov
will pay his first state visit to China on June 9-13, coming at
the invitation of Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The visit will raise bilateral relations to a higher level.
</P>
<P>
The two countries, though geographically wide apart, cherish a
long tradition of friendship. Bilateral cooperation in politics,
the economy, culture, science and technology has proceeded
smoothly since diplomatic relations were established in October
1993.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Gligorov met President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng
in Moscow and Copenhagen respectively. Later in the year, Former
Foreign Minister Stevo Crvenkovski visited China.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
made his first visit to the Balkan country, and it was followed by
Macedonian Economic Minister Bekir Zuta's China tour.
</P>
<P>
During these visits, Macedonian leaders vowed to continue to
implement the "one China" policy. They hoped China would achieve
reunification through its "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade, though growing rather slowly in recent years,
never ceases to gain momentum and faces a bright prospect.
</P>
<P>
Several Chinese trade delegations have lately explored the
possibility for more cooperation with Macedonia and a trade
delegation is to come to China with President Gligorov.
</P>
<P>
During this visit, the two sides will sign agreements on
investment protection and avoiding double taxation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, cooperation in other sectors has been boosted
enormously.
</P>
<P>
China sent students, martial arts coaches and scholars to
Macedonia. It also provided humanitarian aid to Macedonia to
relieve its heavy burden of refugees.
</P>
<P>
In return for this, Macedonia made donations to China's
flood-stricken areas. All these exchanges and mutual help will, as
Gligorov said in an interview, usher in "a broader and brighter
era" for the friendly ties linking the two peoples. 
</P>
</TEXT>
