<HEADLINE> Macedonia, China Enjoy Prospect to Develop Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov
said there is a bright and wide prospect for the Macedonian-Sino
cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy to have received the official invitation of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin to visit friendly China. Our nation
attaches great importance to my forthcoming visit," Gligorov said
in an interview with Xinhua before his Chinese trip on June 9-13,
the first one by a Macedonian president.
</P>
<P>
A smooth development of the Macedonian-Sino diplomatic
relations helps growth in other links between the two countries
and Macedonia is ready at all times to conduct extensive
cooperation with China on international occasions, said he.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the best friends of Macedonia, an important
factor in the international affairs, a honest partner in
mutual-benefit cooperations, said Gligorov.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that after my China's visit, there must be coming a
wider and brighter stage of the friendly and cooperative
cooperations between the two countries, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian president praised China's reform and open-door
policy which he said has become a positive and successful example
in the world. He wished that his country and China will further
strengthen economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of China's foreign policy based farsighted
strategic stand, saying Macedonia must learn from China in this
respect.
</P>
<P>
On Macedonia's internal situation, he noted that the Republic
of Macedonia is a part of the Balkan region. Macedonia has avoided
war, consolidated its independence, achieved democracy and legal
system and carried out reforms in politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
In the economic field, Macedonia has been privatized state
enterprises. Its currency and market are stable.
</P>
<P>
On its policy with neighboring states, Gligorov pointed out
that Macedonia will develop friendly ties with all neighbors on a
basis of equal distance principle, creating an
mutual-understanding and mutual-trust atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia has established diplomatic and cooperative relations
with its all neighboring states, and it has taken a series of
steps to push forward the Europeanization in the Balkan region,
added the president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
