<DOCNO> XIE19970608.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak to Benefit from Economic Reforms: ADB Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Large fiscal deficit, low foreign
exchange reserves and low domestic saving have been the immediate
challenges for Pakistan's macro-economic policy.
</P>
<P>
This was stated in the Asian Development Bank's (ADB) annual
report for 1997-98 fiscal year issued here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
In the next two years, "Pakistan is likely to benefit from the
ongoing reforms and from the improvement in the economic growth of
its trading partners," said the ADB report.
</P>
<P>
"A more stable political environment should enhance economic
performance", it said.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the report stated, difficult challenges confront
Pakistan's economic managers given the urgent need to reduce the
budget deficit, shore up foreign exchange reserves, and increase
domestic saving.
</P>
<P>
The ADB report said that as a result of reforms in the banking
system now, incentives for small savers, among other things,
should become more effective.
</P>
<P>
Together with an improvement in the domestic economy in the
second half of 1997 and better fiscal management, these reforms
could lead to an increase in gross national saving to 13.3 percent
of the gross national product in 1997 and 14.9 percent in 1998,
the report forecast.
</P>
<P>
Domestic investment could increase as the reduction in the
fiscal deficit frees financial resources for both public and
private investment, it believed.
</P>
<P>
"The unemployment rate is likely to remain at less than five
percent if output growth continues at projected levels. However,
Pakistan is still a labor-surplus economy.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to domestic employment-generation programs, the
government proposes to launch an aggressive program to promote
overseas employment of Pakistani workers. If this program
succeeds, remittances of overseas workers can be expected to
increase over the next two years," the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
