<HEADLINE> Gotti in Sight of Tour of Italy Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Gotti has a sight to clinch the
victory in the Tour of Italy Saturday though he finished second to
closest challenger Pavel Tonkov at the 238km stage.
</P>
<P>
Italian Gotti was 24 hours away from producing his country's
first Giro d'Italia triumph since 1991.
</P>
<P>
